Package com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array.points

Interface FillingArrayPointsArrayNumbers<T extends java.lang.Number>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of numeric data for initializing the coordinates of objects of the class Point.
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface FillingArrayPointsArrayNumbers<T extends java.lang.Number>
    The functional interface declares a contract to filling an array of an object of the Point class by initializing the coordinates of the points with the numeric values of the array.

    Created by Konstantin Lugowoy on 15-Jan-18.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Konstantin Lugowoy

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Point<T>[] fill​(T[] array)
      Fills an array with objects of the Point class by initializing the coordinates with values taken from the numeric array passed to the parameter.
